    • WHY APPLECARE+ - Get protection, service and support direct from Apple. AppleCare+ covers unlimited repairs for accidental damage, like a cracked display, and includes coverage for the hardware and battery. Get convenient service at Apple Stores and Apple Authorized Service Providers around the world or Express Replacement Service so you don’t have to wait for a repair. Help is easy with 24/7 priority tech support from Apple experts.
    • PEACE OF MIND - Each incident is subject to a low service fee of $69 for Apple Watch and $79 for Apple Watch Ultra.
    • AUTOMATIC ACTIVATION - AppleCare+ is a digital purchase that is automatically activated when your device is delivered by Amazon so it’s already protected when it arrives at your door. There is no physical shipment for AppleCare+.
    • PROOF OF COVERAGE EMAIL - You will receive an email from Amazon Marketplace with the AppleCare Proof of Coverage at time of device shipment. This email will contain your AppleCare+ agreement number, attached device serial number, coverage end date and link to the AppleCare+ terms and conditions. For gifts, please forward this email to the owner of the device.
    • EASY ATTACH - AppleCare+ attaches to the purchased device, so if its for you or someone else, you can have peace of mind that the coverage will follow the device.
    • REVIEW COVERAGE DETAILS - Once the device is setup and signed into AppleID, coverage can be reviewed directly on iPhone or iPad in Settings > General > AppleCare & Warranty. You can also see your purchase through Amazon in Your Account > Orders or reference the AppleCare Proof of Coverage email.
    • CANCEL ANYTIME - AppleCare+ coverage is a separate order number from your device order number. If you wish to return, you must cancel AppleCare+ by contacting Amazon Toll free: 1 (888) 280-4331 within 30 days of purchase for a full refund. After 30 days you can contact Apple and get a pro-rated refund (Used service fees will be deducted from the pro-rated refund for a 2 year plan).
    • TERMS & CONDITIONS - Terms & Conditions can be downloaded via Amazon > Your Account > Orders > Software Library or you can visit apple.com/legal/sales-support for details. For additional support, please visit getsupport.apple.com or download the Apple Support app.

    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Great Fitness Companion, but Battery Life Falls Short
    Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2025
    Color: Starlight Aluminum Case with Starlight Sport BandSize: 40mm Case + Small/Medium bandStyle: GPSConfiguration: Without AppleCare+
    The Apple Watch SE (2nd Gen) [GPS, 40mm] is a fantastic smartwatch, especially for those who prioritize health and fitness tracking. Here's a quick breakdown of its most notable features: Key Features: Heart Health Tracking Monitors heart rate... See more
    The Apple Watch SE (2nd Gen) [GPS, 40mm] is a fantastic smartwatch, especially for those who prioritize health and fitness tracking. Here's a quick breakdown of its most notable features:

    Key Features:
    Heart Health Tracking

    Monitors heart rate continuously.
    Sends alerts for unusually high or low heart rates.
    Fitness Tracking

    Tracks workouts like running, cycling, swimming, and more.
    Calorie tracking and daily activity monitoring with the Activity Rings.
    Safety Features

    Fall detection and Emergency SOS.
    Crash detection for added peace of mind.
    Sleep Monitoring

    Tracks sleep stages and offers insights to improve your rest.
    Customizable Workouts

    Integrated with Apple Fitness+ for guided workouts.
    The Downside:
    The biggest letdown is the battery life. It struggles to last more than a day with regular use, especially when using fitness and heart tracking features extensively. This means you’ll need to charge it daily, which can be inconvenient.

    Overall Verdict:

    If you’re looking for a reliable health and fitness companion with solid features, the Apple Watch SE is a great choice. However, the short battery life might be a dealbreaker for some, especially those who need a longer-lasting device for extended tracking.

    This is my first Apple watch. I purchased the SE (2nd Gen) GPS watch. My main purpose was to track my steps since I don't always keep my phone in my pocket. A couple of other reasons...as I am growing older, I thought it would be good to have in case I ever fell when I was home alone and because AFIB runs in my family. I've been wearing the watch for a month and this week it alerted me to an irregular heart beat. I did the sensible thing and went to my doctor who also wears an Apple watch. She said she's seen several people whose watches have alerted them to irregular heart beats.
    I have found so many reasons to like this watch though.....my phone is usually close by; therefore, I can see texts on my watch, accept or decline phone calls. It keeps track of my heart rate and allows me to check it. I can see the date, time, temperature and outdoor weather conditions with a flick of my wrist while the watch remains black other times. I'm certain there are lots of other uses I'm not even aware of; however, it checks off all the boxes for me to be very happy with it. If you've been trying to decide about purchasing one, this one is very reasonably priced and I think you'll be pleased.
    I did purchase separately a magnetic band because it looks a bit dressier and fits my small wrist perfectly.
